Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash}(if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

While the potatoes cook, trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}, carrot and shallot. Stir-fry until everything is browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g} and half the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @beef stock paste{10%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @dried oregano{1}, @sugar{1} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce (see ingredients for both amounts) to the mince, then stir until combined.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the sauce has thickened, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Top with an even layer of mash, then sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{25%g}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When the pie has 5 mins baking time left, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything is ready, share the cottage pie between your plates and serve with the peas alongside. Enjoy!